effectively. It's interesting that this process occurs before `readObject` returns, preventing failures. \\n\\nHowever, I'm concerned about missing metadata for that carrier, especially since it’s a private nested class. If it’s not registered for serialization during native image testing, it might lead to issues. I'm also considering how to handle metadata generation and ensure everything works smoothly across the dynamic workflow.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing metadata and testing**\\n\\nI'm noticing that without metadata, native errors can occur, so it's important that the test runs in Native after Forge merges the metadata. The carrier metadata should be generated by the agent, which I can't edit directly, but that’s okay. I need to implement this in the test. Currently, the direct hook writes a byte array with NoDefault, so I might need to create a new test or modify the hook payload to allow for optional replacements while ensuring valid hook restoration. Changing `writeUsingSerializationHook` to utilize a replacing stream should help with key encoding.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mGIcVlA84gNHvVI4E0CiCV78|fc_0a0fe75d0d3b3ac1016a3fae64f1048190b20a257668817698", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/ProvLMSPrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;", "newText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;"}, {"oldText": "        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutput = new NoDefaultWriteObjectOutputStream(output)) {\n            serializationHook(privateKey.getClass(), \"writeObject\", ObjectOutputStream.class)\n                    .invoke(privateKey, objectOutput);\n        }", "newText": "        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutput = new ReplacingKeyEncodingObjectOutputStream(output)) {\n            serializationHook(privateKey.getClass(), \"writeObject\", ObjectOutputStream.class)\n                    .invoke(privateKey, objectOutput);\n        }"}, {"oldText": "        try (ObjectInputStream objectInput = new NoDefaultReadObjectInputStream(input)) {\n            serializationHook(privateKey.getClass(), \"readObject\", ObjectInputStream.class)\n                    .invoke(privateKey, objectInput);\n        }", "newText": "        try (ObjectInputStream objectInput = new ResolvingKeyEncodingObjectInputStream(input)) {\n            serializationHook(privateKey.getClass(), \"readObject\", ObjectInputStream.class)\n                    .invoke(privateKey, objectInput);\n        }"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class NoDefaultWriteObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        NoDefaultWriteObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream output) throws IOException {\n            super(output);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultWriteObject() {\n            // `ProvLMSPrivateKey` stores its state through explicit `writeObject` calls.\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class NoDefaultReadObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        NoDefaultReadObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream input) throws IOException {\n            super(input);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultReadObject() {\n            // `ProvLMSPrivateKey` restores its state through explicit `readObject` calls.\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static final class ReplacingKeyEncodingObjectOutputStream\n            extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private boolean keyEncodingReplaced;\n\n        ReplacingKeyEncodingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream output) throws IOException {\n            super(output);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultWriteObject() {\n            // `ProvLMSPrivateKey` stores its state through explicit `writeObject` calls.\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (!keyEncodingReplaced && object instanceof byte[] encoding) {\n                keyEncodingReplaced = true;\n                return new EncodedKey(encoding.clone());\n            }\n            return object;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResolvingKeyEncodingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        ResolvingKeyEncodingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream input) throws IOException {\n            super(input);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultReadObject() {\n            // `ProvLMSPrivateKey` restores its state through explicit `readObject` calls.\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof EncodedKey encodedKey) {\n                return encodedKey.encoding().clone();\n            }\n            return object;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private record EncodedKey(byte[] encoding) implements Serializable {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3655, "output": 2422, "cacheRead": 70656, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 76733, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782558277607, "responseId": "resp_0a0fe75d0d3b3ac1016a3fae4633c48190bbba0e9afaecfa57"}}
